    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 10 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sausage-and-red-onion-tart/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the onion is softening, dust your work surface with a sprinkling of <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Unwrap your <strong>puff pastry</strong> and roll it out to approx. 0.5cm thickness with a <strong>rolling pin </strong>and cut into 1 rectangle per person</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sausage-and-red-onion-tart/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Line a baking tray (or two!) with <strong>non-stick baking paper</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>pastry</strong> <strong>rectangle[s]</strong> to the tray[s] and score a 1cm border around the edge of the pastry with a knife</p><p>Prick the inside of the border all over with a fork (this will stop you getting a soggy bottom!)</p><p>Tip: The pastry border will puff up to give you a nice crust!</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sausage-and-red-onion-tart/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>soft cheese</strong> to a bowl with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and mix it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>soft cheese mix</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sausage-and-red-onion-tart/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add <strong>half</strong> your <strong>red wine vinegar</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and cook for a further 2-3 min or until beginning to caramelise \u2013 this is your <strong>caramelised onion</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sausage-and-red-onion-tart/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Spread the <strong>soft cheese mix </strong>over the pastry, keeping it within the borders</p><p>Top with the <strong>caramelised onion</strong> and tear over your <strong>sausage meat </strong>(remove the paper if required!)</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 15 min or until the pork, sage & onion stuffing is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the pastry is golden and cooked through and the edges have puffed up \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy sausage & red onion tart[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sausage-and-red-onion-tart/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the tart[s] is cooking, combine the <strong>remaining red wine vinegar </strong>with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>pepper </strong>in a bowl \u2013 this is your <strong>dressing</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>salad </strong>and pat it dry with kitchen paper, then add it to the dressing<strong> </strong>and give everything a gentle mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>dressed salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sausage-and-red-onion-tart/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy sausage & red onion tart </strong>with the <strong>dressed salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
